National Police Service spokesman Bruno Shioso is among dozens of officers who were promoted by the employer National Police Service Commissions. The officers affected were promoted to the ranks of Assistant Inspector General of Police, Commissioner of Police, Senior Superintendent of Police and Superintendent of police. Among those who got the rank of AIG include Shioso, Nairobi police boss James Mugera, Rift Valley Regional police commander Tom Odero, Central Regional Police boss Manasseh Musyoka, his North Eastern counterpart George Seda, Lazarus Opicho of Judicial Police Unit and head of reforms at DCI Eliud Langat. Director of the Crime Research and Intelligence Bureau, Paul Mumo, and Deputy Director of Forensics Margaret Karanja and Rosemary Kuraru of Inspector General of policeâ€™s office who got the Senior Assistant Inspector General of Police rank. Others were Ziporah Mboroki of DCI Academy and Amos Omuga, while Joseph Ondoro and Linus Owango got the rank of Commissioner of Police. Nairobi Regional Criminal Investigations Officer (RCIO) is Paul Wachira and his Rift Valley counterpart Isaac Meeme were confirmed to the rank of Commissioner of Police. The confirmation of the ranks has been pending for months which affected the delivery of service at large. Officials said more changes are pending and would be announced in a week.